.TH "ata_eh_about_to_do" 9 "ata_eh_about_to_do" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ata_eh_about_to_do \- about to perform eh_action
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ata_eh_about_to_do
.BI "(struct ata_link *link "  ","
.BI "struct ata_device *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int action "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "link" 12
target ATA link
.IP "dev" 12
target ATA dev for per-dev action (can be NULL)
.IP "action" 12
action about to be performed

Called just before performing EH actions to clear related bits
in \fIlink->eh_info\fP such that eh actions are not unnecessarily
repeated.

LOCKING:
None.
